OL,5,CARE YOU HAVING TURKEY THIS CHRISTMAS?  
OL,7, "Turkeys raised on intensive farms are 
OL,8, often kept inCover-crowded conditions,"
OL,9, says Juliet Gellatley from Viva.       
OL,11, "Because of a lack of space, most of   
OL,12, these turkeys will spend their entire  
OL,13, livesCstanding in their own excrement  
OL,14, which causes painful blisters and      
OL,15, ulcers on their breast and feet.       
OL,17, "In addition many will have their      
OL,18,Cbeaks sliced off with a red-hot blade  
OL,19, to prevent them fighting each other."  
